<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|5}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| To the end that the children of Israel may bring their sacrifices, which they offer in the open field, even that they may bring them unto the LORD,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|6}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Unto the priest, and offer them for peace offerings unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|7}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the priest shall sprinkle the blood upon the altar of the LORD,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|8}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And burn the fat for a sweet savour unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|9}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And they shall no more offer their sacrifices unto devils, after whom they have gone a whoring.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|10}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Whatsoever man there be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers which sojourn among you, that offereth a burnt offering or sacrifice,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|11}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And bringeth it not to offer it unto the LORD;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|12}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Even that man shall be cut off from among his people.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|13}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And whatsoever man there be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers that sojourn among you, that eateth any manner of blood;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|14}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I will even set my face against that soul that eateth blood, and will cut him off from among his people.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|15}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For the life of the flesh is in the blood: and I have given it to you upon the altar to make an atonement for your souls:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|16}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For it is the blood that maketh an atonement for the soul.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|17}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Therefore I said unto the children of Israel, No soul of you shall eat blood, neither shall any stranger that sojourneth among you eat blood.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|18}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And whatsoever man there be of the children of Israel, or of the strangers that sojourn among you,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|19}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Which hunteth and catcheth any beast or fowl that may be eaten;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|20}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| He shall even pour out the blood thereof, and cover it with dust.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|21}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For it is the life of all flesh; the blood of it is for the life thereof:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|22}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Therefore I said unto the children of Israel, Ye shall eat the blood of no manner of flesh:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|23}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For the life of all flesh is the blood thereof: whosoever eateth it shall be cut off.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|24}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I am the LORD your God. After the doings of the land of Egypt, wherein ye dwelt, shall ye not do:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|25}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And after the doings of the land of Canaan, whither I bring you, shall ye not do: neither shall ye walk in their ordinances.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|26}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall do my judgments, and keep mine ordinances, to walk therein: I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|27}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall therefore keep my statutes, and my judgments: which if a man do, he shall live in them: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|28}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| None of you shall approach to any that is near of kin to him, to uncover their nakedness: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|29}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| The nakedness of thy father, or the nakedness of thy mother, shalt thou not uncover:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|30}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| She is thy mother; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|31}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| The nakedness of thy father's wife shalt thou not uncover: it is thy father's nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|32}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| The nakedness of thy sister, the daughter of thy father, or daughter of thy mother,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|33}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Whether she be born at home, or born abroad, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|34}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| The nakedness of thy son's daughter, or of thy daughter's daughter, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|35}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| For theirs is thine own nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|36}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| The nakedness of thy father's wife's daughter, begotten of thy father, she is thy sister, thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|37}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father's sister: she is thy father's near kinswoman.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|38}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy mother's sister for she is thy mother's near kinswoman.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|39}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father's brother, thou shalt not approach to his wife: she is thine aunt.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|40}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy daughter in law: she is thy son's wife; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|41}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy brother's wife: it is thy brother's nakedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|42}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her daughter,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|43}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither shalt thou take her son's daughter, or her daughter's daughter, to uncover her nakedness;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|44}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| For they are her near kinswomen: it is wickedness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|45}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither shalt thou take a wife to her sister, to vex her, to uncover her nakedness, beside the other in her life time.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|46}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Also thou shalt not approach unto a woman to uncover her nakedness, as long as she is put apart for her uncleanness.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|47}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Moreover thou shalt not lie carnally with thy neighbour's wife, to defile thyself with her.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|48}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| And thou shalt not let any of thy seed pass through the fire to Molech,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|49}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|50}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Thou shalt not lie with mankind, as with womankind: it is abomination.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|51}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither shalt thou lie with any beast to defile thyself therewith:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|52}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither shall any woman stand before a beast to lie down thereto: it is confusion.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|53}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Defile not ye yourselves in any of these things: for in all these the nations are defiled which I cast out before you:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|54}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| And the land is defiled: therefore I do visit the iniquity thereof upon it, and the land itself vomiteth out her inhabitants.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|55}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Ye shall therefore keep my statutes and my judgments, and shall not commit any of these abominations;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|56}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Neither any of your own nation, nor any stranger that sojourneth among you:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|57}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| (For all these abominations have the men of the land done, which were before you, and the land is defiled;)}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|58}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| That the land spue not you out also, when ye defile it, as it spued out the nations that were before you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|59}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| For whosoever shall commit any of these abominations, even the souls that commit them shall be cut off from among their people.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|60}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| Therefore shall ye keep mine ordinance, that ye commit not any one of these abominable customs, which were committed before you,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|61}}</small>{{font|color=#000088| And that ye defile not yourselves therein: I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|62}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall be holy: for I the LORD your God am holy.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|63}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall fear every man his mother, and his father, and keep my sabbaths: I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|64}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Turn ye not unto idols, nor make to yourselves molten gods: I am the LORD your God.}}

