<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|164}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| He shall be holy unto thee: for I the LORD, which sanctify you, am holy.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|165}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the daughter of any priest, if she profane herself by playing the whore, she profaneth her father: she shall be burnt with fire.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|166}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shall he go in to any dead body, nor defile himself for his father, or for his mother;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|167}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shall he go out of the sanctuary, nor profane the sanctuary of his God;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|168}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he shall take a wife in her virginity.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|169}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| A widow, or a divorced woman, or profane, or an harlot, these shall he not take:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|170}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But he shall take a virgin of his own people to wife.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|171}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shall he profane his seed among his people: for I the LORD do sanctify him.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|172}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Whosoever he be of thy seed in their generations that hath any blemish, let him not approach to offer the bread of his God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|173}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For whatsoever man he be that hath a blemish, he shall not approach:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|174}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| A blind man, or a lame, or he that hath a flat nose, or any thing superfluous,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|175}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Or a man that is brokenfooted, or brokenhanded,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|176}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Or crookbackt, or a dwarf, or that hath a blemish in his eye, or be scurvy, or scabbed, or hath his stones broken;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|177}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Only he shall not go in unto the vail, nor come nigh unto the altar, because he hath a blemish;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|178}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That he profane not my sanctuaries: for I the LORD do sanctify them.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|179}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That they separate themselves from the holy things of the children of Israel,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|180}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And that they profane not my holy name in those things which they hallow unto me: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|181}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Whosoever he be of all your seed among your generations,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|182}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That goeth unto the holy things, which the children of Israel hallow unto the LORD, having his uncleanness upon him,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|183}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That soul shall be cut off from my presence: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|184}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| What man soever is a leper, or hath a running issue; he shall not eat of the holy things, until he be clean.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|185}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And whoso toucheth any thing that is unclean by the dead, or a man whose seed goeth from him;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|186}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Or whosoever toucheth any creeping thing, whereby he may be made unclean,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|187}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Or a man of whom he may take uncleanness, whatsoever uncleanness he hath;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|188}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| The soul which hath touched any such shall be unclean until even, and shall not eat of the holy things, unless he wash his flesh with water.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|189}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And when the sun is down, he shall be clean, and shall afterward eat of the holy things; because it is his food.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|190}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That which dieth of itself, or is torn with beasts, he shall not eat to defile himself therewith; I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|191}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| They shall therefore keep mine ordinance, lest they bear sin for it, and die therefore, if they profane it: I the LORD do sanctify them.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|192}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| There shall no stranger eat of the holy thing: a sojourner of the priest, or an hired servant, shall not eat of the holy thing.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|193}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But if the priest buy any soul with his money, he shall eat of it, and he that is born in his house: they shall eat of his meat.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|194}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| If the priest's daughter also be married unto a stranger, she may not eat of an offering of the holy things.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|195}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But if the priest's daughter be a widow, or divorced, and have no child, and is returned unto her father's house, as in her youth,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|196}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| She shall eat of her father's meat: but there shall be no stranger eat thereof.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|197}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if a man eat of the holy thing unwittingly, then he shall put the fifth part thereof unto it,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|198}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And shall give it unto the priest with the holy thing.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|199}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And they shall not profane the holy things of the children of Israel, which they offer unto the LORD;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|200}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Or suffer them to bear the iniquity of trespass, when they eat their holy things: for I the LORD do sanctify them.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|201}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Whatsoever he be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers in Israel, that will offer his oblation for all his vows,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|202}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And for all his freewill offerings, which they will offer unto the LORD for a burnt offering;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|203}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall offer at your own will a male without blemish, of the beeves, of the sheep, or of the goats.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|204}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But whatsoever hath a blemish, that shall ye not offer: for it shall not be acceptable for you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|205}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And whosoever offereth a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the LORD to accomplish his vow, or a freewill offering in beeves or sheep,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|206}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| It shall be perfect to be accepted; there shall be no blemish therein.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|207}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Blind, or broken, or maimed, or having a wen, or scurvy, or scabbed, ye shall not offer these unto the LORD,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|208}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Nor make an offering by fire of them upon the altar unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|209}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Either a bullock or a lamb that hath any thing superfluous or lacking in his parts,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|210}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That mayest thou offer for a freewill offering; but for a vow it shall not be accepted.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|211}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall not offer unto the LORD that which is bruised, or crushed, or broken, or cut; neither shall ye make any offering thereof in your land.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|212}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither from a stranger's hand shall ye offer the bread of your God of any of these;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|213}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Because their corruption is in them, and blemishes be in them: they shall not be accepted for you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|214}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| When a bullock, or a sheep, or a goat, is brought forth, then it shall be seven days under the dam;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|215}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And from the eighth day and thenceforth it shall be accepted for an offering made by fire unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|216}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And whether it be cow, or ewe, ye shall not kill it and her young both in one day.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|217}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And when ye will offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving unto the LORD, offer it at your own will.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|218}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| On the same day it shall be eaten up; ye shall leave none of it until the morrow: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|219}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Therefore shall ye keep my commandments, and do them: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|220}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shall ye profane my holy name; but I will be hallowed among the children of Israel: I am the LORD which hallow you,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|221}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|222}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall bring a sheaf of the firstfruits of your harvest unto the priest:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|223}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he shall wave the sheaf before the LORD, to be accepted for you:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|224}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| On the morrow after the sabbath the priest shall wave it.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|225}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall offer that day when ye wave the sheaf an he lamb without blemish of the first year for a burnt offering unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|226}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the meat offering thereof shall be two tenth deals of fine flour mingled with oil, an offering made by fire unto the LORD for a sweet savour:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|227}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the drink offering thereof shall be of wine, the fourth part of an hin.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|228}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall eat neither bread, nor parched corn, nor green ears, until the selfsame day that ye have brought an offering unto your God: shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|229}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| It shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|230}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall count unto you from the morrow after the sabbath, from the day that ye brought the sheaf of the wave offering;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|231}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Seven sabbaths shall be complete: even unto the morrow after the seventh sabbath shall ye number fifty days;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|232}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall offer a new meat offering unto the LORD. Ye shall bring out of your habitations two wave loaves of two tenth deals;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|233}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| They shall be of fine flour; they shall be baken with leaven; they are the firstfruits unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|234}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall offer with the bread seven lambs without blemish of the first year, and one young bullock, and two rams:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|235}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| They shall be for a burnt offering unto the LORD, with their meat offering, and their drink offerings,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|236}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Even an offering made by fire, of sweet savour unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|237}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then ye shall sacrifice one kid of the goats for a sin offering, and two lambs of the first year for a sacrifice of peace offerings.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|238}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the priest shall wave them with the bread of the firstfruits for a wave offering before the LORD, with the two lambs:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|239}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| They shall be holy to the LORD for the priest.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|240}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not make clean riddance of the corners of thy field when thou reapest,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|241}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shalt thou gather any gleaning of thy harvest: thou shalt leave them unto the poor, and to the stranger: I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|242}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Whosoever curseth his God shall bear his sin.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|243}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he that blasphemeth the name of the LORD, he shall surely be put to death, and all the congregation shall certainly stone him:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|244}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| As well the stranger, as he that is born in the land, when he blasphemeth the name of the Lord, shall be put to death.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|245}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he that killeth any man shall surely be put to death.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|246}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he that killeth a beast shall make it good; beast for beast.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|247}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if a man cause a blemish in his neighbour; as he hath done, so shall it be done to him;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|248}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Breach for breach, eye for eye, tooth for tooth: as he hath caused a blemish in a man, so shall it be done to him again.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|249}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And he that killeth a beast, he shall restore it: and he that killeth a man, he shall be put to death.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|250}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall have one manner of law, as well for the stranger, as for one of your own country: for I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|251}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| The land shall keep a sabbath unto the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|252}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Six years thou shalt sow thy field, and six years thou shalt prune thy vineyard, and gather in the fruit thereof;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|253}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But in the seventh year shall be a sabbath of rest unto the land, a sabbath for the LORD:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|254}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Thou shalt neither sow thy field, nor prune thy vineyard.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|255}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| That which groweth of its own accord of thy harvest thou shalt not reap, neither gather the grapes of thy vine undressed:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|256}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For it is a year of rest unto the land.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|257}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the sabbath of the land shall be meat for you;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|258}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For thee, and for thy servant, and for thy maid, and for thy hired servant, and for thy stranger that sojourneth with thee.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|259}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And for thy cattle, and for the beast that are in thy land, shall all the increase thereof be meat.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|260}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And thou shalt number seven sabbaths of years unto thee, seven times seven years;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|261}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the space of the seven sabbaths of years shall be unto thee forty and nine years.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|262}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then shalt thou cause the trumpet of the jubile to sound on the tenth day of the seventh month,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|263}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall hallow the fiftieth year, and proclaim liberty throughout all the land unto all the inhabitants thereof: it shall be a jubile unto you;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|264}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall return every man unto his possession, and ye shall return every man unto his family.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|265}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| In the year of this jubile ye shall return every man unto his possession.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|266}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if thou sell ought unto thy neighbour, or buyest ought of thy neighbour's hand, ye shall not oppress one another:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|267}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| According to the multitude of years thou shalt increase the price thereof,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|268}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And according to the fewness of years thou shalt diminish the price of it:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|269}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For according to the number of the years of the fruits doth he sell unto thee.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|270}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall not therefore oppress one another; but thou shalt fear thy God:for I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|271}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Wherefore ye shall do my statutes, and keep my judgments, and do them; and ye shall dwell in the land in safety.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|272}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And the land shall yield her fruit, and ye shall eat your fill, and dwell therein in safety.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|273}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye shall say, What shall we eat the seventh year? behold, we shall not sow, nor gather in our increase:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|274}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then I will command my blessing upon you in the sixth year, and it shall bring forth fruit for three years.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|275}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall sow the eighth year, and eat yet of old fruit until the ninth year; until her fruits come in ye shall eat of the old store.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|276}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And in all the land of your possession ye shall grant a redemption for the land.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|277}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| If thy brother be waxen poor, and hath sold away some of his possession,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|278}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if any of his kin come to redeem it, then shall he redeem that which his brother sold.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|279}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if thy brother be waxen poor, and fallen in decay with thee; then thou shalt relieve him:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|280}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Yea, though he be a stranger, or a sojourner; that he may live with thee.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|281}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Take thou no usury of him, or increase: but fear thy God; that thy brother may live with thee.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|282}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Thou shalt not give him thy money upon usury, nor lend him thy victuals for increase.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|283}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I am the LORD your God, which brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, to give you the land of Canaan, and to be your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|284}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if thy brother that dwelleth by thee be waxen poor, and be sold unto thee; thou shalt not compel him to serve as a bondservant:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|285}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And then shall he depart from thee, both he and his children with him,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|286}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And shall return unto his own family, and unto the possession of his fathers shall he return.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|287}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Thou shalt not rule over him with rigour; but shalt fear thy God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|288}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if a sojourner or stranger wax rich by thee, and thy brother that dwelleth by him wax poor,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|289}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And sell himself unto the stranger or sojourner by thee, or to the stock of the stranger's family:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|290}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And as a yearly hired servant shall he be with him: and the other shall not rule with rigour over him in thy sight.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|291}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For unto me the children of Israel are servants; they are my servants whom I brought forth out of the land of Egypt:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|292}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|293}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall make you no idols nor graven image, neither rear you up a standing image,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|294}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Neither shall ye set up any image of stone in your land, to bow down unto it: for I am the LORD your God.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|295}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Ye shall keep my sabbaths, and reverence my sanctuary: I am the LORD.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|296}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| If ye walk in my statutes, and keep my commandments, and do them;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|297}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then I will give you rain in due season, and the land shall yield her increase, and the trees of the field shall yield their fruit.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|298}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And your threshing shall reach unto the vintage, and the vintage shall reach unto the sowing time:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|299}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall eat your bread to the full, and dwell in your land safely.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|300}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will give peace in the land, and ye shall lie down, and none shall make you afraid:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|301}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will rid evil beasts out of the land, neither shall the sword go through your land.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|302}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall chase your enemies, and they shall fall before you by the sword.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|303}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And five of you shall chase an hundred, and an hundred of you shall put ten thousand to flight:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|304}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And your enemies shall fall before you by the sword.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|305}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| For I will have respect unto you, and make you fruitful, and multiply you, and establish my covenant with you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|306}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall eat old store, and bring forth the old because of the new.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|307}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I set my tabernacle among you: and my soul shall not abhor you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|308}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will walk among you, and will be your God, and ye shall be my people.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|309}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I am the LORD your God, which brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, that ye should not be their bondmen;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|310}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I have broken the bands of your yoke, and made you go upright.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|311}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| But if ye will not hearken unto me, and will not do all these commandments;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|312}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye shall despise my statutes, or if your soul abhor my judgments,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|313}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| So that ye will not do all my commandments, but that ye break my covenant: I also will do this unto you;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|314}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I will even appoint over you terror, consumption, and the burning ague, that shall consume the eyes, and cause sorrow of heart:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|315}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall sow your seed in vain, for your enemies shall eat it.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|316}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will set my face against you, and ye shall be slain before your enemies:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|317}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| They that hate you shall reign over you; and ye shall flee when none pursueth you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|318}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye will not yet for all this hearken unto me, then I will punish you seven times more for your sins.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|319}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will break the pride of your power; and I will make your heaven as iron, and your earth as brass:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|320}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And your strength shall be spent in vain: for your land shall not yield her increase, neither shall the trees of the land yield their fruits.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|321}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye walk contrary unto me, and will not hearken unto me; I will bring seven times more plagues upon you according to your sins.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|322}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| I will also send wild beasts among you, which shall rob you of your children, and destroy your cattle, and make you few in number;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|323}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And your high ways shall be desolate.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|324}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye will not be reformed by me by these things, but will walk contrary unto me;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|325}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then will I also walk contrary unto you, and will punish you yet seven times for your sins.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|326}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will bring a sword upon you, that shall avenge the quarrel of my covenant:}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|327}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And when ye are gathered together within your cities, I will send the pestilence among you; and ye shall be delivered into the hand of the enemy.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|328}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And when I have broken the staff of your bread, ten women shall bake your bread in one oven,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|329}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And they shall deliver you your bread again by weight: and ye shall eat, and not be satisfied.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|330}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And if ye will not for all this hearken unto me, but walk contrary unto me;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|331}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then I will walk contrary unto you also in fury; and I, even I, will chastise you seven times for your sins.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|332}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And ye shall eat the flesh of your sons, and the flesh of your daughters shall ye eat.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|333}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will destroy your high places, and cut down your images,}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|334}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And cast your carcases upon the carcases of your idols, and my soul shall abhor you.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|335}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will make your cities waste, and bring your sanctuaries unto desolation, and I will not smell the savour of your sweet odours.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|336}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will bring the land into desolation: and your enemies which dwell therein shall be astonished at it.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|337}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And I will scatter you among the heathen, and will draw out a sword after you: and your land shall be desolate, and your cities waste.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|338}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Then shall the land enjoy her sabbaths, as long as it lieth desolate, and ye be in your enemies' land;}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|339}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| Even then shall the land rest, and enjoy her sabbaths.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|340}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| As long as it lieth desolate it shall rest; because it did not rest in your sabbaths, when ye dwelt upon it.}}

<small>{{font|color=#0000FF|341}}</small>{{font|color=#000000| And upon them that are left alive of you I will send a faintness into their hearts in the lands of their enemies;}}

